From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 07:05:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ==== data activity monitor ====

mm/damon: monitor multiple data acitivities

DAMON monitors only data access activities.  This limits usage of DAMON.
Using DAMOS_STAT and filters, users can get more detailed page level
information.  It is still constrained to DAMOS filter types and induce
high overhead.

Extend DAMON to monitor not only data access activities but multiple
types of activities.  Allow users to register multiple data activities
of their interest.  Allocate that number of counters to the regions and
increment the counter every sampling intervals if the activity was made
onsample memory of the region.  The regions adjustment is be done with a
user-defined primary activity.

The activity of interests are registered as multiple chains of DAMOS
filter-like filters.  It has type, matching, allow, and additional
parameters.  The type supports page table walk, page faults, perf event,
access event details (accessor CPU, cgroup, task, read, write), and page
properties (anon, file-backed, unmapped, belonging cgroup, ...).

When an activity of interests are registered, nr_accesses like user ABI
files are just making no effect.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
